node.title: Victoria records 1,126 new COVID-19 cases and five deaths
node.alt: An orange sticker on pavement showing the direction to a vaccination clinic
node.description: There are now 16,178 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 366 people have died during the current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,126 new local COVID-19 cases and five deaths.", "There are now 16,178\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 366\u00a0people have died during the current Delta outbreak.", "There are 556 COVID-19 patients in hospital in Victoria, of whom 91 are in intensive care and 54 are on a ventilator.", "The new cases were detected from 44,479\u00a0test results processed on Sunday.", "The health department says about 84 per cent of Victorians aged 12 and older have now been fully vaccinated.", "The state's restrictions will ease again once 90 per cent of Victorians aged 12+ have been fully vaccinated, which is expected to occur around November 24.", "More to come.", "", "
How to take a rapid antigen test
"]
